problem_data.title: Permutations II
problem_data.description: Given a collection of numbers, nums, that might contain duplicates, return all possible unique permutations in any order.
problem_data.solution:
class Solution(object):
    def permuteUnique(self, nums):
        """
        :type nums: List[int]
        :rtype: List[List[int]]
        """
        res = []
        nums.sort()  # 先排序方便去重
        used = [False] * len(nums)

        def backtrack(path):
            if len(path) == len(nums):
                res.append(path[:])
                return
            for i in range(len(nums)):
                if used[i]:
                    continue
                if i > 0 and nums[i] == nums[i-1] and not used[i-1]:
                    continue  # 避免重複排列
                used[i] = True
                path.append(nums[i])
                backtrack(path)
                path.pop()
                used[i] = False

        backtrack([])
        return res
